        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 7:41AM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A band of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility to
less than one mile.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 741 AM EDT, a band of heavy snow was along
a line extending from S.B. Elliot State Park to near Karthaus to
Centre Hall and moving southeast at 35 MPH.

THIS BAND OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Houserville, Lecontes Mills, and Seven Mountains around 745 AM
EDT.
Black Moshannon State Park, Plymptonville, and Clearfield around
750 AM EDT.
Woodland and State College around 755 AM EDT.
Park Forest Village around 810 AM EDT.

For those driving on Interstate 80, this includes areas between the
Dubois Route 255 and Snow Shoe exits, specifically from mile markers
106 to 145.

This includes Interstate 99 between mile markers 67 and 68, and from
mile markers 70 to 84.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
